<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb575f38f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s285j–2"><num value="285j–2">§ 285j–2.</num><heading> Bioengineering research</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director of the Institute shall make grants or enter into contracts for research on the means to overcome paralysis of the extremities through electrical stimulation and the use of computers.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb575f390-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373">July 1, 1944, ch. 373</ref>, title IV, § 459, as added <ref href="/us/pl/99/158/s2">Pub. L. 99–158, § 2</ref>, <date date="1985-11-20">Nov. 20, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/857">99 Stat. 857</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
